Sec. 164.083. FAILURE TO TREAT FOR SCABIES.
commits an offense if the person:
Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

- 944 -

(a)

A person

AGRICULTURE CODE

(1) owns, controls, or cares for cattle or sheep infected
with scabies or cattle or sheep that have been exposed to scabies
infection within six months prior to the date of an order to treat
under Section 164.021; and
(2) fails or refuses to treat the sheep or cattle at the
time and in the manner provided by the order of the commission.
(b) An offense under this section is a Class B misdemeanor.
(c) A person commits a separate offense for each day of failure
or refusal.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1426, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1,
Amended by Acts 1989, 71st Leg., ch. 836, Sec. 45, eff. Sept.
1989.
